Yearly Analysis of Temperature Variation in Mumbai over Five Years

Importing the original dataset

dataset = read.csv("bombay.csv")

Since,it doesn’t snow at all in Mumbai due to it’s geographical location, the column Total_Snow_In_cm has been removed.

dataset = dataset[-c(5)]

Applying the Multiple Linear Regression Model

model <- lm(tempC ~
            maxtempC + mintempC  + sunHour + uvIndex + uvIndex.1+ moon_illumination
+ DewPointC
+ FeelsLikeC

+ HeatIndexC
+ WindChillC
+ WindGustKmph
+ cloudcover
+ humidity
+ precipMM
+ pressure

+ visibility
+ winddirDegree
+ windspeedKmph
  , data = dataset )
summary(model)

Extracting the yearly data from the original dataset.

data1 <- dataset[ which(dataset$date_time >='1/1/2015  00:00:00 AM' & dataset$date_time <'1/1/2016  00:00:00 AM'), ]

data2 <- dataset[ which(dataset$date_time >='1/1/2016  00:00:00 AM' & dataset$date_time <'1/1/2017  00:00:00 AM'), ]

data3 <- dataset[ which(dataset$date_time >='1/1/2017  00:00:00 AM' & dataset$date_time <'1/1/2018  00:00:00 AM'), ]

data4 <- dataset[ which(dataset$date_time >='1/1/2018  00:00:00 AM' & dataset$date_time <'1/1/2019  00:00:00 AM'), ]

data5 <- dataset[ which(dataset$date_time >='1/1/2019  00:00:00 AM' & dataset$date_time <'1/1/2020  00:00:00 AM'), ]

data6 <- dataset[ which(dataset$date_time >='1/1/2020  00:00:00 AM'),]
